The paper discusses a novel method for improving the resolution/volume/speed trade-off in electron microscopy, which involves innovative data acquisition and algorithmic techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories, as these fields often deal with image processing and analysis. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the data mining (cs.DM), graphics (cs.GR), and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories, as these fields may involve similar techniques for processing and analyzing large amounts of data.
